Boot Button Switch
==================

|Product| has one switch on the board marked as SW1, shown in the figure below. |br|
When press the button before power on, the Raspberry Pi will boot from the USB connector. You can use this function to download the OS software to the internal eMMC. |br|
When release the button before power on, or ignore the button when you power, the Raspberry Pi will boot from internal eMMC.

There is no need to alter the Button switch settings during regular operation. However, if you need to reinstall the OS, please refer to the detailed information on how to re-flash the OS from the :ref:`Software Documentation <Pi_OS>`.

.. figure:: /Media/Pi/A72/CS10600RA4070/BootButton_V2.jpg
  :figclass: align-center
  :align: center

  *Boot Button Switch*